I think that, if it's not already done, it's important that you know that you will always meet people who will not necessarily agree with your choices, who will not like your style, your mannerisms or I don't know what else... but, never stop believing in yourself, stay as you are, with your personality and your sensitivity that seduced the jury; Another thing, it's not given to everyone to dare! It will allow you to move forward and we can only note that you go with any repertoire, I even find your versions sometimes better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you were not part of the one on whom I would have bet at the start and honestly, I don't remember not having appreciated one of your performances, I find you amazing... to finish, I really liked your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I had liked the original too but for once I heard the lyrics clearly, we maybe had a little impression that you were paying attention not to make any mannerisms, you transmitted me emotion through my television so I don't understand that 3 members of the jury did not feel it! There you go, I wish you all the best, keep your feet on the ground, don't change anything about what you are, stay humble, stay you, make good use of constructive criticism and don't pay attention to those that are not.
